<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="46" pageNumber="47">The original specimens of the variety are still present in the Berlese Collection, viz. the nos. 208/26, 27 (type), 29, 30; they originate from Lake City, Florida.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="46" pageNumber="47">The variety differs from the species in structure of tegument, colour, and size. In Florida the variety is, according to Jacot (1933, p. 242), more common than the typical species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
